+      "evidence": "The same `getReadRangeFromProps(...); readAllData(..., readRanges[0][0], readRanges[1][1], ...)` sequence is now repeated in both production and test code, and `readAllData` depends on four correlated slice arguments (`dataFiles`, `statsFiles`, `startOffsets`, `endOffsets`) staying in sync.",
+      "change_request": "Seems no need to push prop lookup into every caller; can we keep one canonical helper or pass a named read-range object so `readAllData` still owns this storage-specific preparation?"
+    },
+    {
+      "severity": "Minor",
+      "title": "`readAllData`'s new `endOffsets` parameter name overstates what the function actually does",
+      "why": "The new signature reads as if both offset arrays bound the actual file reads, but only `startOffsets` is passed to `readOneFile`. `endOffsets` is used only to estimate size and pick concurrency.",
