+      "evidence": "After the signature change, `readAllData` computes `size := endOffsets[i] - startOffsets[i]` and logs `endOffset`, but the downstream call at `reader.go:111-126` still forwards only `startOffsets[fileIdx]` into `readOneFile`. No name or comment explains that `endOffsets` is only a sizing or concurrency hint.",
+      "change_request": "Please rename this parameter to something that matches its role, such as `rangeEstimateEndOffsets`, or add a short why-comment stating that the values are only used for concurrency estimation and logging, not as hard read bounds."
+    },
+    {
+      "severity": "Minor",
